requires python2-virtualenv

~~ ODDITIES 

* Installs in virtualenv in /opt/graphene
* Includes uwsgi server because I don't want to have to mess w/Apache

~~ PORTS

Open to UDP from any source: 8125 (statsd listener)
Open to TCP from localhost only: 2003 (graphite listener)
Open to TCP from approved hosts only: 81 (Graphite dashboard)

~~ INSTALL

useradd --home /opt/graphite --shell /bin/false graphite

virtualenv --distribute --system-site-packages /opt/graphite

/opt/graphite/bin/pip-2.7 install carbon whisper graphite-web uwsgi Django tagging NOTE SEE GRAPHITE.INSTALL FOR LATEST DEPS

CREATE carbon.conf AND storage-schemas.conf
CREATE THE uWSGI DJANGO INI FILE /opt/graphene/conf/uwsgi-graphite.yaml
CREATE webapp/graphite/local_settings.py

chown graphite /opt/graphite -R

/opt/graphite/bin/python /opt/graphite/webapp/graphite/manage.py syncdb

~~ RUNNING

statsd
rc.d start statsd

Carbon
/opt/graphite/bin/carbon-cache.py start

uWSGI Server running Graphite
/opt/graphite/bin/uwsgi --yaml /opt/graphite/conf/uwsgi-graphite.yaml
